Privacy Policy
Last updated: December 26, 2022
I value your privacy and make decisions in our development to respect it to the best of our ability. This Privacy Policy describes Our policies and procedures on the collection, use and disclosure of Your information when You use the Service.
Blueterminal
stores data entered by you locally on the devices you use to interact with the service. No data is sent to external servers or third party apps.
No Personally-Identifying Information is transmitted to external locations when using
Blueterminal
.
No Bluetooth device identification is stored when using
Blueterminal
. The Bluetooth information used is limited to the usage of the app and no information gets stored locally or in external servers.
Blueterminal
may offer the opportunity to purchase additional functions and/or features from within the application (an “In-App Purchase”). All billing and transaction processes are handled by the provider of the Application Store (the “App Store Provider”) from whose platform Customer downloaded the Software and are governed by the App Store Provider’s terms and conditions. If Customer has any payment related issues with In-App Purchases, then Customer must contact the App Store Provider directly.
If you have a question about this privacy and how your data are collected, used and stored when using
Blueterminal
, please feel free to email me at
blueterminalapp@gmail.com
with the subject line
